cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.RO

The paper discusses a multi-agent model of the organism Physarum polycephalum, which involves computational methods and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to generate representations of the external and internal shapes of a set of points. The behaviour of the plasmodium is mediated by environmental stimuli, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also explores potential morphological computation approaches, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
